---
By: Irina Tweedie
Locus:
  Page: 470
  Verse: 7
Tags:
  - Thoughts
---
If we only knew deeply, absolutely, that our smallest act, our smallest
thought, has such far-reaching effects; setting forces in motion; reaching
out to the galaxy; how carefully we would act and speak and think. How
precious life would become in its integral wholeness.
